traceRecord.$descriptionTemplate: Trace records correspond to server logs
traceRecord.onlySid.$description: Only the creator's session actions are traced in this record
traceRecord.isSessionConcerned.$descript: Visual information that allows to know if the current session is concerned by the record.
traceRecord.sessionId.$description: Visual information that allows to know what session is concerned by the record
traceRecord.ticket.$description: This information is not mandatory. It only make easier Sage support analysis when you will send traces files.
traceRecord.contents.$description:
Traces that are recording are not able to be used until it will be flushed.
Traces files are automatically compressed.
traceRecord.configs.$description: Any change on an automatic record configuration will be used as default one by following automatic records.
traceRecord.$services.test.$description:
Only available in development mode !!!
This will write new traces following 'test' configuration
traceRecord.$services.testAll.$descripti:
Only available in development mode !!!
This will write new traces following 'test' configuration and then propagate same writes on every processes handled by the load balancer.
traceRecord.$services.flush.$description: Can be called manually to allow to analyse traces.
traceRecord.$services.download.$descript: Concatenate every traces content in one compressed file.
traceContent.size.$description: This is the uncompressed file size
traceSetting.$descriptionTemplate: Default traces settings used by records
traceSetting.$service.reset.$confirm: This operation will reset configuration elements with factory values
